OL,3,CMurdered ex-prison officer's family
OL,4,Cpraised for 'determined' law change
OL,5,Ccampaign
OL,7,F"I pause here to again pay tribute to
OL,8,Fformer prison custody officer Lenny
OL,9,FScott as well as his family, who I am
OL,10,Fmeeting tomorrow (Tuesday), for their
OL,11,Fdignified and determined advocacy on
OL,12,Fhis behalf."
OL,14,FThe Bill suffered only one defeat
OL,15,Fduring its passage through the Lords,
OL,16,Fwith peers demanding that victims of
OL,17,Fserious crimes have swift and free
OL,18,Faccess to the judge's sentencing
OL,19,Fremarks in their cases.
